id: pm-6vv6
title: "writeFileAtomic cross-device rename safety: handle EXDEV when tmp and target are on different mounts"
description: "writeFileAtomic writes a .tmp file in the same directory as the target then renames. If the item store is on a different filesystem mount than the temp-file directory (e.g. symlinked paths, container bind mounts, or network FS), fs.rename raises EXDEV (cross-device link not permitted). There is no fallback to copy+unlink."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: "area:storage",correctness,durability
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:02:44.972Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T10:15:53.139Z"
author: audit-data-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- `writeFileAtomic` catches `EXDEV` and falls back to: write to a tmp in `os.tmpdir()`, copy to target, unlink tmp\n- OR falls back to a non-atomic `writeFile` with a warning so the file is never left corrupt\n- Both `fs-utils.ts` and the LanceDB snapshot writer handle this case\n- Unit test covering the EXDEV code path (mock `rename` to throw EXDEV)"
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: low
confidence: high
body: "## Context\n\n`src/core/fs/fs-utils.ts:29-38`:\n```ts\nawait fs.writeFile(tempPath, contents, 'utf8');\nawait fs.rename(tempPath, targetPath);\n```\n\nOn Linux/macOS, `rename(2)` is atomic within a filesystem but raises `EXDEV` across mounts. The same temp-in-same-dir pattern is used for both the LanceDB snapshot (`src/core/search/vector-stores.ts:458-477`) and the drift cache (`src/core/history/drift-scan.ts`). Any deployment where `.agents/pm/` is a bind mount or symlink to a different device will see silent write failures on every mutation.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `writeFileAtomic` catches `EXDEV` and falls back to: write to a tmp in `os.tmpdir()`, copy to target, unlink tmp\n- [ ] OR falls back to a non-atomic `writeFile` with a warning so the file is never left corrupt\n- [ ] Both `fs-utils.ts` and the LanceDB snapshot writer handle this case\n- [ ] Unit test covering the EXDEV code path (mock `rename` to throw EXDEV)\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/core/fs/fs-utils.ts:29-38` — no EXDEV handling\n- `src/core/search/vector-stores.ts:456-478` — `persistLanceDbLocalTable` also uses writeFile+rename without EXDEV handling"
